@hsu you can't simulate the SA fisheye cameras with the current gazebo cameras using flat projection (well, you can, but it results in a fairly bad rendering). Using such a large angle results in an extremely distorted image. In order to simulate a fisheye lens like the SA cameras have you'll need a simualted fisheye camera. To see the difference see [these examples](http://strlen.com/gfxengine/fisheyequake/compare.html), and [this image](http://i.imgur.com/imlQlyd.jpg) to see what it looks like in gazebo right now.

A camera with a smaller, less distorted fov would likely be more useful than the current solution until gazebo supports fisheye cameras.

Also, I think the gazebo camera definitions need to go into atlas_v3.gazebo instead of atlas_v3.urdf?
